The City of Ekurhuleni has postponed the election of a new mayor. eNCA/Aviwe Mtila JOHANNESBURG - Nthabiseng Tshivhenga has been elected as the acting speaker of Ekurhuleni once again. Tshivhenga was up against former speaker Raymond Dhlamini but he did not get the support he needed. READ: Ekurhuleni council | DA's Raymond Dhlamini removed as speaker Dhlamini was removed as speaker of the Ekurhuleni council on Thursday. The motion was brought by the self-proclaimed Super Seven - an ANC-aligned coalition of smaller parties in the metro.